    title: "Final Mechanicals & Exterior Completion",
    description: "Complete all mechanical installations and exterior site work to make the house fully functional and ready for occupancy.",
    content: `
<div class="module-content">
  <section class="learning-objectives">
    <h2>Learning Objectives</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Master final electrical and plumbing fixture installation</li>
      <li>Understand HVAC system startup and balancing</li>
      <li>Learn concrete and landscaping completion</li>
      <li>Navigate final mechanical inspections</li>
      <li>Coordinate exterior site work and cleanup</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>This stage involves the final installation of all mechanical fixtures and the completion of the exterior site work. The house is now fully functional and the property is taking its final form.</p>

    <h3>Electrician Final Work</h3>
    <h4>Device Installation</h4>
    <p>Outlets, switches, and cover plates are installed in all electrical boxes. Light fixtures are installed in all locations. The doorbell, smoke detectors, and carbon monoxide detectors are installed and tested.</p>

    <h4>Appliance Connections</h4>
    <p>The electrician makes the final connections for hardwired appliances (oven, cooktop, dishwasher, garbage disposal).</p>

    <h4>Panel Labeling</h4>
    <p>All circuits in the electrical panel are clearly labeled.</p>

    <h3>Plumber Final Installation</h3>
    <h4>Fixture Installation</h4>
    <p>Sinks, faucets, toilets, and showerheads are installed. The garbage disposal and dishwasher are connected. The washing machine hookups are completed.</p>

    <h4>Water Heater</h4>
    <p>The water heater is installed and connected to the water supply, drain, and power/gas.</p>

    <h4>Testing</h4>
    <p>All fixtures are tested for proper operation and leaks.</p>

    <h3>HVAC Contractor Final Tasks</h3>
    <h4>Register and Grille Installation</h4>
    <p>Supply registers and return air grilles are installed in all rooms.</p>

    <h4>Thermostat Installation</h4>
    <p>The thermostat is installed and wired to the furnace/air handler.</p>

    <h4>System Startup and Testing</h4>
    <p>The HVAC system is started up, tested, and balanced to ensure proper airflow and temperature control in all rooms.</p>

    <h3>Concrete Contractor Work</h3>
    <h4>Driveway and Walkways</h4>
    <p>Forms are set for the driveway and walkways. A gravel base is compacted, and concrete is poured and finished. Control joints are cut to control cracking.</p>

    <h4>Patio</h4>
    <p>If a concrete patio is specified, it is poured and finished.</p>

    <h3>Landscaper Responsibilities</h3>
    <h4>Final Grading</h4>
    <p>The lot is graded to its final contours, ensuring proper drainage away from the house. Topsoil is spread in planting areas.</p>

    <h4>Irrigation System</h4>
    <p>An underground sprinkler system is installed (if specified).</p>

    <h4>Planting</h4>
    <p>Sod, grass seed, trees, shrubs, and other plants are installed according to the landscape plan.</p>

    <h4>Mulch and Edging</h4>
    <p>Mulch is spread in planting beds, and edging is installed to define borders.</p>

    <h3>City Inspector Requirements</h3>
    <h4>Final Mechanical Inspections</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Final Electrical:</strong> The inspector tests outlets for proper wiring and grounding, checks that all fixtures are installed correctly, and verifies panel labeling.</li>
      <li><strong>Final Plumbing:</strong> The inspector checks all fixtures for proper installation and operation, tests for leaks, and verifies proper venting.</li>
      <li><strong>Final HVAC:</strong> The inspector verifies proper installation of equipment, ductwork, and venting, and may test the system for operation.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Final Grading Inspection</h4>
    <p>The inspector verifies that the lot is graded to drain water away from the foundation and that erosion control measures are in place.</p>

    <h3>Construction Manager Role</h3>
    <h4>Scheduling</h4>
    <p>The CM schedules the final installations for all mechanical trades and coordinates the concrete and landscaping work.</p>

    <h4>Inspection Coordination</h4>
    <p>The CM schedules all final mechanical inspections and the grading inspection.</p>

    <h4>System Testing</h4>
    <p>The CM ensures that all systems (electrical, plumbing, HVAC) are fully tested and operational.</p>

    <h4>Site Cleanup</h4>
    <p>The CM oversees the cleanup of the construction site, including removal of all debris, equipment, and temporary structures.</p>
  </section>
</div>
